cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is about text summarization, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also introduces a new model for summarization, which involves iterative learning and selective reading, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also likely sub-categories.
